That the pressure of the rotated air gradually diminishes from the outer edge to the centre of the vortex, 1 gather from the following. For when all the particles of the atirial whirlpool strive to recede from the centre, it results that they impel and press against the particles of air adjacent to them on the -outside; while, on the contrary, the air between them and the centre of the vortex is subjected to less pres- sure from them now than while as yet they had no circular motion and no tendency to recede from the -centre of their motion.
